  <section>
    <h2>‚ùì Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: Will updating reset my WiFi password?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Usually no. Most routers preserve WiFi settings during updates. However, some updates do reset settings, which is why backing up is important.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: Will my DNS filtering (OpenDNS/CleanBrowsing) still work after updating?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Sometimes. Many firmware updates reset DNS settings to automatic/ISP defaults. Always check and re-enter DNS addresses after updating.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: How often should I update firmware?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Check every 3-6 months for routine updates. Install security updates immediately when announced. Enable automatic updates if available.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: Can I update over WiFi?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Technically possible but NOT recommended. WiFi connections can drop during the update, potentially bricking the router. Always use Ethernet cable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: My router is 5+ years old. Should I update or replace?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> If manufacturer still provides updates, update it. If discontinued (no updates for 1+ years), consider replacing for security. Modern routers support WPA3, WiFi 6, and better filtering.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: What if I can't find firmware for my router?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Your router may be discontinued. Check manufacturer website thoroughly, contact support, or consider alternative firmware (OpenWrt, DD-WRT) if supported. Otherwise, upgrade to a newer model.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: The update failed. Is my router ruined?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Not necessarily. Try recovery mode specific to your router brand. If that fails, try factory reset. Most routers can recover from failed updates if you follow the correct recovery procedure.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Q: Should I enable automatic firmware updates?</h4>
        <p><strong>A:</strong> Pros: Ensures timely security patches without manual intervention. Cons: Updates might reset DNS filtering or other custom settings. Recommendation: Enable auto-update but check DNS settings weekly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

